<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in one’s day • on one’s day</xh5><p> <i>in one’s day</i>—(also: in one’s days) 1. during one’s lifetime: And did not he [Bacon] cling to geocentricism, which was still prevailingly current <u>in his day</u>? 2. in a period of one’s success, prosperity, etc.: I know of one eminent man of science, who was a burning and shining light <u>in his day</u>.</p><p><i>on one’s day—</i>when performing as well as one can: <u>On his day</u> he’s the finest goalkeeper in the country.</p> </entry>
